tldr: The user requested a review of a sleep questionnaire application against
  its acceptance criteria and the implementation of missing features. The agent
  successfully added a tiredness severity scale, COMISA and Insufficient Sleep
  Syndrome detection, outbound resource links, weighted EDS scoring, expanded
  CSV export, and pain/chronic fatigue screening questions.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to ensure all acceptance criteria were met and to
  implement any identified missing features. The agent conducted a detailed
  analysis, identifying several critical gaps. The implementation phase focused
  on enhancing the questionnaire's diagnostic capabilities and data utility. Key
  additions included a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness, complete with safety
  warnings for high scores, and sophisticated detection logic for complex sleep
  disorders like COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. The agent also
  integrated valuable outbound links to external sleep and mental health
  resources, improved the accuracy of Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) scoring
  with weighted calculations, and significantly expanded the CSV export
  functionality to capture all questionnaire data. Furthermore, new questions
  were introduced to screen for pain severity and chronic fatigue, providing a
  more holistic patient assessment. The approach involved systematic updates
  across types, validations, UI components, and report generation logic,
  ensuring a robust and feature-rich application.
